### Mermaid diagram — `sz-diagram`

A fenced ` ```mermaid ` block renders as an interactive diagram, with an enlarge button that opens a zoom/pan overlay so dense graphs stay legible.

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  A[Markdown] --> B{Build}
  B -->|11ty| C[Web · HTML]
  B -->|Go| D[TUI over SSH]
  C --> E[Reader]
  D --> E
```

### Inline copy chip — `sz-copy`

Click-to-copy for commands and snippets. Copies the `text` attribute, falling back to its slotted text: <sz-copy>ssh stephan.zych.be</sz-copy>

### Outline rail — `sz-toc`

A sticky outline (scroll-spy: highlights the current section, click to jump) plus a thin top progress bar. It reads headings straight from the rendered page, so it needs no data — auto-injected above every article body; drop `<sz-toc>` to add it elsewhere.

